bilingual.source: His hair is always in a mess.
His room is always in a mess.
Her desk looks very in a mess.
bilingual.target: 她的书桌看起来非常杂乱。

bilingual.source: Why did you make the kitchen so in a mess?
bilingual.target: 你为什么让厨房变得这么杂乱？

bilingual.source: The once beautiful garden has degenerated into a wild mess.
bilingual.target: 曾经美丽的花园已经退化成一片杂乱。

bilingual.source: After the kids played, the living room was in a mess.
bilingual.target: 孩子们玩完后，客厅一片杂乱。

bilingual.source: "There's a lot to do, "Henry thought, as he looked at the mess in the kitchen.
bilingual.target: "有很多事要做，"亨利看着杂乱的厨房，心里想。

bilingual.source: Said at downright ugly mess on one of the markets!
bilingual.target: 说难听点简直就一杂乱的菜市场！

bilingual.source: We cannot have what we want without going through the mess.
bilingual.target: 没有经历这些消极杂乱状况，我们就不会得到我们想要的。

bilingual.source: Looking for my key in the mess of the desk is like finding a needle in a haystack.
bilingual.target: 在杂乱的书桌上找我的钥匙就像是大海捞针一般。

list.abstract: MESS是北京一家售卖高端潮流品牌的店铺品牌名。
MESS是一个英文单位，有混乱、困境、食堂、肮脏等意思。

yingyinNormal.en: And clean up this mess.
yingyinNormal.zh: 还有去收拾下这烂摊子。
yingyinNormal.videoNameEn: 《Rise of the Planet of the Apes》

yingyinNormal.en: Those guys don't mess around.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他们可不是吃干饭的。

yingyinNormal.en: Yeah, you don't want to mess with this one.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是啊，你不会想惹她的。

yingyinNormal.en: Jesus, Ross. What a mess. We gave you everything.
yingyinNormal.zh: 天呐，罗斯，真是一团糟，我们什么都给你了。

yingyinNormal.en: Sorry about the mess, I don't usually get visitors.
yingyinNormal.zh: 真不好意思，这里乱七八糟的，我这很少有来访者。

yingyinNormal.en: This Jordan Valley thing's a mess. He's in big trouble.
yingyinNormal.zh: 约旦河谷真是一团糟。他有大麻烦了。

yingyinNormal.en: Don't mess with me. What, you're working with Robertson?
yingyinNormal.zh: 别耍我，你跟罗伯森一起工作？

yingyinNormal.en: Make sure he gets there. I have his mess to clean up.
yingyinNormal.zh: 帮我盯着他，我还得帮他收拾烂摊子。

yingyinNormal.en: How did it go? Fine. I think. I didn't mess my bit up.
yingyinNormal.zh: 音乐会怎么样？我觉得挺好的，起码我没犯错。

yingyinNormal.en: Look, you did the right thing last night. I was a mess.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你昨晚的做法是正确的，我当时脑子不清楚。

yingyinNormal.en: Very good. I'm just off to visit Granny and Grandpa Pig. I'll see you later. And please, don't make a mess. Mess? Goodbye. Goodbye.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那太好了。那我就出发去看猪爷爷和猪奶奶了。我们一会儿见。千万别把房子给弄乱了。怎么会？再见。再见。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, Daddy pig, look at the mess you're in. It's only mud.
yingyinNormal.zh: 噢看呐，猪爸爸，瞧瞧你身上多脏啊。

yingyinNormal.en: We recall with our feelings. Anything real should be a mess.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你得勾起人内心的感受。真实的记忆应该是一团乱麻。

yingyinNormal.en: A map. To Skywalker himself? You are right back in the mess.
yingyinNormal.zh: 一张能找到天行者的地图？你是打算重出江湖了。

yingyinNormal.en: And, before you answer, consider the consequences. If we mess up the supply rendezvous, we die. If we mess up the Earth gravity assist, we die.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在你回答去不去之前，想想后果。 如果我们在对接补给的时候没搞好，我们都得死，如果我们没能好好的借助地心引力，我们也是死。

yingyinNormal.en: Mom and Dad got us into this mess. They can pay to get us out.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是爸妈让我们置于这种境地，他们得出钱让我们离开。

yingyinNormal.en: Fine. But after tonight, we need to get a handle on this mess.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，但今晚过后，我们就得好好整理这衣橱。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, trying to turn me on by making a mess? Know your audience.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好，想用把东西弄乱来让我性奋吗？多了解一下你的对象。

yingyinNormal.en: Now, this is last minute so I want to apologize for the mess. Okay?
yingyinNormal.zh: 事出突然，抱歉，房里一团乱。

yingyinNormal.en: Now she knows I'm a desperate mess instead of just being pretty sure.
yingyinNormal.zh: 以前还只是特别怀疑，现在她是明确知道我是个缺爱男了。

word_usage.usage:
mess常与副词up连用，mess up sth./mess sth. up表示“把…弄糟；胡乱地做”、“使不整洁；弄脏；弄乱”。例：
When politicians mess things up, it is the people who pay the price 
政客们把事情搞砸的时候，埋单的是老百姓。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 着重指令人无能为力或感到绝望的混乱状态。突出没有很好的组织。
指东西搅混在一起, 凌乱得难以辨认; 也可指思想混乱, 以致无法进行正常的思维活动。
正式用词, 含义广泛。指事物因失去原有的秩序而造成混乱; 也可指社会中的动乱或骚乱。
主要指社会中政治性的动乱、骚乱; 也可指个人或少数人的闹事。
语气强, 口语中较常用的非正式用词。指既混乱又肮脏, 尤指人思想混乱或外表不整洁。
